Not all keygens are detected as virus's, so  your point is moot.

It usually comes down to the wrapper used to protect the keygens etc which confuses some AV's that it is a virus/trojan through their heuristic systems.

But then again it wouldn't be the first time a lesser known group have added nasties to their releases.
